Your current code is only checking for a `&quot;9&quot;`, because all other checks are over written.

To fix your code (without changing it much), you must do a logical `AND`, so in English it would read like *nameF doesn&#39;t contain &quot;0&quot; AND doesn&#39;t contain &quot;1&quot; AND ...*, like this:

    boolean checkF=true;
    checkF &amp;= nameF.contains(&quot;0&quot;);
    checkF &amp;= nameF.contains(&quot;1&quot;);
    // etc

But what about non-letter non-digits, like a comma? You&#39;ve not preventing that.

